Zambia Aims to Build Two Power Plants Costing $295 Million, Regulator Says

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-05-06T08:16:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/zambia-aims-to-build-two-power-plants-costing-295-million-regulator-says.html
Zambia’s Energy Regulation Board
approved the construction of two power plants that will cost a
total $295 million, said Kwali Mfuni, spokeswoman for the
Lusaka-based regulator.  Itezhi Tezhi Power Corp. and Ndola Energy Co. were given
permission to build new plants, Mfuni said in an e-mailed
statement.  Zambia’s is  Africa ’s biggest copper producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
